The paper focuses on algorithms and experiments for the visualization of directed graphs, which falls under the category of graph drawing and visualization (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the important problem of showing and storing transitivity information of very large graphs and databases, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). The algorithms presented in the paper are based on concepts and frameworks, which suggests a focus on theoretical and algorithmic aspects, falling under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
